cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on using natural language processing and machine learning techniques to extract chemical insights from large collections of documents related to energetic materials. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to extract relevant information from the text, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning algorithms for classification and clustering of chemical compounds and their properties suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of large text corpora, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it involves the social and ethical implications of using natural language processing techniques to extract information from scientific literature.
